cs.PL, cs.OS, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DS 

The paper describes the design and implementation of a functional package manager, which involves programming language concepts and operating system concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also mentions the support for a complete GNU/Linux distribution, which falls under the category of cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper discusses the use of an embedded domain-specific language (EDSL) to describe and compose packages, which is related to software engineering and falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions the use of Scheme as its programming interface, which is related to machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of garbage collection, which is related to data structures and algorithms and falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
